	   <a name=103867515837704></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103867515837704><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5402&mid=103867515837704>Highly Underrated Item for Non Twink Warriors</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5402&mid=103867515837704#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=750><span id= >Hassan</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 30th 12:15 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For players like me who do not twink their characters, this is a surprisingly good item for Warriors.<br><br>First, soloing the Cave Bat Lord is easily done as a Warrior only 1 level higher than the Lord. In a group, it's simplicity, so a mid 20's Warrior can easily get the hat.<br><br>While there are a great many Warrior items with amazing Armor Class, the fact is until higher (30+) levels, the loss of AC is more than compensated for by the Agility and Dexterity boosts. The Int boost is an added bonus of sorts...few Warrior items raise Int, Int is usually a Warriors lowest stat, and Int is critical in raising skill points for ALL classes (ever notice how hard it is as a Troll to raise your skills)<br><br>Not bad at all for those who don't view EQ as a never ending quest to be Uber.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
