<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=102994538883461></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102994538883461><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5402&mid=102994538883461>Chanties</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5402&mid=102994538883461#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=181632><span id= >GhosteDeini</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 21st 12:08 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I've been hunting this guy with my 31 chanter for a while. For all the chanters out there - YOU MUST DO THIS QUEST! why? Because first of all, the belt is a magic item, not lore...so you can collect a lot of them to sell if you have the time. Secondly, we chanters have no need to worry about faction - just cast Benevolence on Azzar and youre good to hand in his hat. And finally, it is one of the few belts (maybe the only one at early levels) that has an INT statistic. So, obviously, there is a good demand for it, especially those who cannot afford the other INT belts. So, as a chanter, I advise all other chanters to do this quest - its very rewarding and we don't have to go through all the trouble of getting faction standings like other classes. I usually run through and just camp the cave bat lord - the other kobolds dont bother me at lvl 31. Hope this helps yall<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
