	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 19th 2:01 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The hat isn't the result of the quest, it's a component in the Black Lace Sash quest. Basically:<br><br>You go into the warrens and kill the batlord. He drops Azzar's Dreadful Hat. The name implies it belongs to someone. It does. Take the hat and give it to Azzar Habbib, a High level Necromancer just inside the newbie gate, (he's in the building up the stairs overlooking the newbie ground). You give him the hat. He likes you and gives you the Black Lace Sash as a reward. You say 'thanks Azzar' or you just leave like I did.<br><br>Or... He doesn't like you and gives you a punch in the nose... or his pet does.<br><br>Thats it. Thats the quest.<br><br>It takes a lot of kobold deaths to get him to like you. The hard part in the quest isn't getting the hat at all, the easy part is getting the hat. The hard part is handing in the hat to the guy to get the sash. However once he likes you, it becomes relatively cinchy to do.<br><br>Rhiante<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jun 19 13:53:50 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
