	   <tr><td colspan=2>Been working on this quest for about a week I guess.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bat Lord was a relatively easy kill for a 26 Wiz, and dropped the hat the first time...but...getting faction up enough so I could turn it in was a little harder.<br><br>First I tried invising myself and handing the hat to Azzar from behind.  But his pet spotted me, and I barely made it out of there in one piece. So I farmed Kolbolds.  It took 711 kills of various mobs in Warrens to raise myself up to dubious ... all in all probably 24 hours of continuous Kolbold killing.  <br><br>For you Wizzies out there, I would get a group of greens to aggro on me with my awesome meleeing skill and then drop cast force followed by column of lightning or shock of ice at whomever ran away (depending on how many lived).  <br><br>I also would kill which ever blue mobs popped when I was around ... these blues are a well kept secret, each would give me about a full blue bubble exp and were pretty easy to root'n'nuke.  They gave me 27 and are probably are enough for me to solo well past 30, but they are starting to get old.  If I die anytime soon and can't get a rez, I might come back for them.  3 blue mobs == Exp lost from one poorly executed plan.<br><br>I also managed to collect a whole stack of barbequed eurodite (+3 INT when eaten) in the process, and also got me a Batling Eye (+2 INT, Range Slot ... not too shabby) but I never saw the Muglwamp (who I hear is a lot of fun).<br><br><br>Good Luck ... and Go Get Your Belt!<br><br><br>-- Alikaar<br>   27 Lvl Wiz of Tarrew Mar<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Apr  4 19:56:09 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>--Alikaar of Tarew Marr<br></td></tr>
