	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 2nd 10:52 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is my basic experience with the quest.<br><br>I began trying to improve my faction at level 12, and it took me till level 17 to become dubious and do it. It took me a bit longer because I had suffered faction losses killing Elial Brook 20 times. Someone had let me loot the hat, though, and since it was no use to me otherwise, I began trying to hand it in after that.<br><br>I am now an ally with the heretics&nbsp;&nbsp;and have handed in the hat a few times. It's a hard quest for a few reasons.<br><br>Firstly, anyone who isn't an evil heretic or has good heretic faction will find it rather difficult to hand in to ole Azzar, since the hat is nodrop. I think Azzar himself is level 45 or so, and scowly to almost everyone. Cammoing and sneaking is an option but you face death if anything goes wrong. Also, under 20s won't be able to do it, as the bat is rather tough even at 25, and getting past the level 20-24 kobolds in the throne room on the way to the batlord is tough (they see through cammo AND invis and there are a lot of them). <br><br>However, once you get around the level limit and faction obstacles it becomes all to easy to do, and I managed to get a sash for all my friend's caster's, and my own which is about 6 sashes. It's a nice little caster sash, but unless you need a lot of them, or you're already amiable with the Heretics, it's better just buying it off someone for 100pp-- it saves a lot of time.<br><br>Sometimes if the batlord has the hat, he starts looking a bit like a bat-- pig-looking-snout, bat ears, and wing flaps. about 8 times out of 10, he will have the hat on him when you loot if he looks like that. (<i>Unless</i> he has a wicker helm on him, instead--both will show the batlike features). Looking batty is a good indication, but there are times he looks batty and won't have anything, though. I've never seen him look normal and have the hat, but I suppose it's possible too.<br><br>Anyway-- it's not a rare spawn-- for every 10 kills, he'll probably drop the hat about 6 times. The spawn rate is 45 minutes pretty much on the minute. Just keep killing him and it will drop.<br><br>Oh, and If you're looking to become dubious with the heretics, the higher end kobolds give better faction hits, and the named even better. Rather than just killing every kobold you see, camp the named if you can.<br><br>Hope that helps!<br><br><br>Rhiante Wylite<br>Luclin<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 16 00:26:42 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
