	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sometimes if your level is to high, You get a message that the foe was a trivial kill, and the item doesn't drop. <br><br>I know this to be true in the warrens where I went with my Level 12 ranger, yesterday, to kill Kobolds for molars, but none dropped. Kept getting a message of "that was a trivial kill for your party." Someone explained that my level was too high and that someone with a lower level had to kill the target for the molars to drop. If I helped or gave it the killing blow, they wouldn't drop the molars.<br><br>He pulled the Bat Lord for me and my party, and he (lvl 20 rogue) beat the crap out of it and zoned for us to finish off the bat. The bad lord is tough. It had around 20 life left, and we COULD NOT hit it to finish it off. I have a 8dmg magic weapon, and hit for 10-18-- but everything we tried was futile. Us being me with my 12 ranger and&nbsp;&nbsp;My paladin friend (also 12). The bat lord had a SLIVER of life left, and we had full life, but try as we might we couldn't finish it off. Kept hitting for like 2, and 3-- He kept hitting me for like 40 a go, until I almost lost all of my 300 HP-- and it still had like 10 hp left. My paladin had to lay hands me to survive, and the killing blow was given to the bat soon afterwards. <br><br>But survive I did! And because we were low level, the bat dropped Azzars hat, and the rogue who pulled let me have it. So it does drop, albeit not for high levels. If you want the items in the warren's, you're going to have to make a character even or blue with the NPC, for it to drop. Would be good to go with a high friend so he can beat it up and zone, and you can finish it off so it drops, or you can enlist the help of lower level people in the warrens and split the loot like the rogue did with us. <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br><br></td></tr>
